modules.description: This module sets up and executes test suites in a browser environment, attaching test runners to document load events and displaying results. It works with `Webtest.Suite.t` structures to define and run test cases. Concrete use cases include automating UI component validation and verifying client-side logic during development.

This module provides functions to execute test suites in a browser environment, integrating with document load events to automate test execution. It works with `Webtest.Suite.t` to define and run test cases, focusing on validating UI components and client-side logic. Concrete use cases include automated testing of web interfaces and verifying JavaScript-compiled OCaml code behavior in real browsers.
